						<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en"><span dir="auto">Tecla Access/Switch Event Provider</span></h1>
						<div id="bodyContent">
								<div id="siteSub">From IDRC Mobile Wiki</div>
								<div id="contentSub"><span class="subpages">&lt; <a href="/Tecla_Access" title="Tecla Access">Tecla Access</a></span>(Redirected from <a href="/index.php?title=Tekla/Switch_Event_Provider&amp;redirect=no" title="Tekla/Switch Event Provider">Tekla/Switch Event Provider</a>)</div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-navigation">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:402px;"><a href="/File:Android_app_architecture.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/2/22/Android_app_architecture.png/400px-Android_app_architecture.png" width="400" height="216" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/2/22/Android_app_architecture.png/600px-Android_app_architecture.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/22/Android_app_architecture.png/800px-Android_app_architecture.png 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/File:Android_app_architecture.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>Architecture of the Android Tekla input method. The Switch Event Provider is a service that receives switch events via bluetooth from the Arduino board and broadcasts them to the OS.</div></div></div>
<p>The Switch Event Provider (SEP) is a Service included with the Android Tekla App. The SEP is responsible for managing the Bluetooth connection with the <a href="/Tekla_Shield" title="Tekla Shield" class="mw-redirect">Tekla Shield</a> and broadcasting switch events to the Tekla IME as well as other 3rd-party applications.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><div id="toctitle"><h2>Contents</h2></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#Features"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Features</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="#API"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">API</span></a>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-3"><a href="#Intents_.28Control.29"><span class="tocnumber">2.1</span> <span class="toctext">Intents (Control)</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-4"><a href="#Actions_.28Broadcasts.29"><span class="tocnumber">2.2</span> <span class="toctext">Actions (Broadcasts)</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-5"><a href="#Extras"><span class="tocnumber">2.3</span> <span class="toctext">Extras</span></a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-6"><a href="#Switch_Event_Flow"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">Switch Event Flow</span></a></li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Features">Features</span></h2>
<ul>
<li> Prevents connection timeouts using the data echoing function on the Shield
</li>
<li> Scans for, and automatically reconnects to, the last Tekla Shield successfully connected if the connection is dropped
</li>
<li> Exposes API to third party applications in the Android phone
</li>
</ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="API">API</span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Intents_.28Control.29">Intents (Control)</span></h3>
<table>
<tr>
<th> Intent
</th>
<th> Namespace String
</th>
<th> Description
</th>
<th> Extras
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> Start SEP
</td>
<td> <code>ca.idi.tekla.sep.SEPService</code>
</td>
<td> Use with startService() to initiate a connection to a Tekla Shield. If no shield MAC address is provided, the SEP will attempt a connection with the last successfully connected Shield.
<p>Even if the connection attempt is unsuccessful, the SEP will periodically attempt a connection to a Shield until it is explicitly stopped.
</p>
</td>
<td> Shield Address
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> Stop SEP
</td>
<td> <code>ca.idi.tekla.sep.SEPService</code>
</td>
<td> Use with stopService() to permanently drop the connection to a Tekla Shield.
</td>
<td> None
</td></tr></table>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Actions_.28Broadcasts.29">Actions (Broadcasts)</span></h3>
<table>
<tr>
<th> Action
</th>
<th> Namespace String
</th>
<th> Description
</th>
<th> Extras
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> SEP Broadcast Started
</td>
<td> <code>ca.idi.tekla.sep.action.SEP_BROADCAST_STARTED</code>
</td>
<td> Intent broadcasted by the SEP when it has started receiving data from the Tekla Shield.
</td>
<td> None
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> SEP Broadcast Stopped
</td>
<td> <code>ca.idi.tekla.sep.action.SEP_BROADCAST_STOPPED</code>
</td>
<td> Intent broadcasted by the SEP when it has stopped receiving data from the Tekla Shield (the connection dropped).
</td>
<td> None
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> Switch Event Received
</td>
<td> <code>ca.idi.tekla.sep.action.SWITCH_EVENT_RECEIVED</code>
</td>
<td> Intent broadcasted by the SEP when receiving a switch event from the Tekla Shield.
</td>
<td> Switch Event
</td></tr></table>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Extras">Extras</span></h3>
<table>
<tr>
<th> Extra
</th>
<th> Namespace String
</th>
<th> Type
</th>
<th> Description
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> Shield Address
</td>
<td> <code>ca.idi.tekla.sep.extra.SHIELD_ADDRESS</code>
</td>
<td> String
</td>
<td> Optional MAC address of the Shield to connect to.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> Switch Event
</td>
<td> <code>ca.idi.tekla.sep.extra.SWITCH_EVENT</code>
</td>
<td> Integer
</td>
<td> The nature of the switch event received according to the table below.
</td></tr></table>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Switch_Event_Flow">Switch Event Flow</span></h2>
<div class="ibox" style="background: #FFEED9; border: 1px solid #BB0000; padding: 5px 5px 5px 5px; width: 80%; margin-left: auto; margin-right:auto; border-radius: 7px; -moz-border-radius: 7px;">
<table style="background: #FFEED9; border: 0px">
<tr>
<td> <div class="MediaTransformError" style="width: 40px; height: 0px; display:inline-block;">Error creating thumbnail: Unable to save thumbnail to destination</div>
</td>
<td> <b>This method of broadcasting switch events will be deprecated in favor of a more generic approach exposing all switch states on every state change. Helper labelled masks will be provided to expose user switch preferences to 3rd.-party applications</b>
</td></tr></table>
</div><br />
<table>
<tr>
<th> ACU / Switch Box
</th>
<th colspan="2">Tekla Shield
</th>
<th colspan="2">Arduino
</th>
<th> Bluetooth Interface
</th>
<th> Android
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th> Event
</th>
<th> Port / Pin # changed
</th>
<th> Pin changed to
</th>
<th> Pin # changed
</th>
<th> Pin changed to
</th>
<th> Byte Sent
</th>
<th> Switch Event Extra
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> Switch released
</td>
<td> Any previously closed
</td>
<td> Open
</td>
<td> D8-12
</td>
<td> HIGH
</td>
<td> <code>0x0F</code>
</td>
<td> 160
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> Right switch pressed
</td>
<td> DE9 / 4
</td>
<td> Closed to common
<p>(Pin# 8)
</p>
</td>
<td> D8
</td>
<td> LOW
</td>
<td> <code>0x0E</code>
</td>
<td> 80
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> Left switch pressed
</td>
<td> DE9 / 3
</td>
<td> Closed to common
<p>(Pin# 8)
</p>
</td>
<td> D9
</td>
<td> LOW
</td>
<td> <code>0x0D</code>
</td>
<td> 40
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> Back/Down switch pressed
</td>
<td> DE9 / 2
</td>
<td> Closed to common
<p>(Pin# 8)
</p>
</td>
<td> D10
</td>
<td> LOW
</td>
<td> <code>0x0B</code>
</td>
<td> 20
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> Forward/Up switch pressed
</td>
<td> DE9 / 1
</td>
<td> Closed to common
<p>(Pin# 8)
</p>
</td>
<td> D11
</td>
<td> LOW
</td>
<td> <code>0x07</code>
</td>
<td> 10
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> Extra 1 pressed
</td>
<td> 3.5mm plug / tip
</td>
<td> Closed to base
</td>
<td> D12
</td>
<td> LOW
</td>
<td> <code>0x1F</code>
</td>
<td> 8
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> Extra 2 pressed
</td>
<td> 3.5mm plug / ring
</td>
<td> Closed to base
</td>
<td>&#160;??
</td>
<td> LOW
</td>
<td> <code>0x2F</code>
</td>
<td> 16
</td></tr></table>

